# Dynamic Segments

You can capture values from the URL using `:paramName` in the path. They are available in `req.params`.

```javascript
app.get('/users/:userId', (req, res) => {
  const userId = req.params.userId;
  res.send(`User ID: ${userId}`);
});
```

Visiting `/users/42` → `User ID: 42`.

You can have multiple parameters: `/posts/:postId/comments/:commentId`

## Accessing Query Parameters

Query string values (after `?` in the URL) are available in `req.query`.

```javascript
app.get('/search', (req, res) => {
  const term = req.query.q;
  const page = req.query.page || 1;
  res.send(`Searching for ${term}, page ${page}`);
});
```

Request: `/search?q=node&page=2` → `Searching for node, page 2`.

`req.query` is an object with parsed query parameters.

